{"key":"post-7082046","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>7082046</id>\n<content>Don't use pesticices.  Grow enough for you and the bugs.  Harvest early before the caps open, and flies won't have had a chance to lay eggs into the gills, thus no maggots.  You can throw some copper wire or pennies on the ground around the patch to repel slugs.  They hate to crawl over copper.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next></next>\n<prev>7081366</prev>\n<first>7079552</first>\n<last>7082046</last>\n<when>1182577733</when>\n<utime>06/23/07 08:48 AM</utime>\n</post>"}